parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: resulting in a loss of power and control; the vehicle may jerk or sputter before stalling; the engine may make a loud noise before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Stop Car Immediately Coolant Low" warning appears on the dashboard; the vehicle overheats; the coolant level drops rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporative emission system can cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, which can lead to engine damage or stalling if not addressed.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates; the vehicle may experience poor fuel economy or performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the driveshaft to crack, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: A bend or crack in the exhaust system is discovered during routine maintenance; the vehicle may experience poor performance or unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pressure switch can cause the engine to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent sudden loss of power at high speeds
"Reduced Engine Performance" message on the dashboard
and a strong pulsing action and sound from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic fuel pump module can cause the engine to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. Corrosion of the module due to its placement on the outside of the vehicle can exacerbate the problem.
symptoms: "Reduced Engine Performance" message on the dashboard
and a strong pulsing action and sound from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the fuel pump flange can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires and potentially cause accidents.
Intermittent engine stalling can cause a loss of control and potentially lead to accidents.
The sudden failure of the tire sidewall can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
